# Service Account Analytical Agent Consistency Check

## Purpose

Use this checklist to test whether the Service Account Analytical Agent produces stable, source-aware and caveated outputs over time.

It helps prevent the agent from changing definitions, forgetting caveats, overstating confidence or treating exploratory service account analysis as governed truth.

## Strategic OS North Star

> Increase strategic opportunities by helping leaders make better strategic decisions.

The Service Account Analytical Agent is only useful if it improves analytical judgement consistently.

## When To Use

Use this checklist when:

- creating or reviewing the Service Account Analytical Agent
- changing service account source rules
- changing metric definitions
- changing metric caveats
- changing Genie context
- reviewing service account analytical reliability
- checking whether service account outputs can support decisions
- investigating inconsistent service account analysis

## Core Principle

The same service account question should receive the same source logic, metric definition, caveats and confidence treatment each time.

The wording may vary.

The governance logic should not.

