## Test Questions

Use repeatable questions to check whether the agent applies source rules, metric definitions and caveats consistently.

| Test Question | Purpose | Expected Source Logic | Expected Caveat |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| What is service account volume? | Tests metric definition and grain handling | Confirm source and grain before interpretation | Grain must be confirmed |
| Are active service accounts increasing? | Tests active-status logic and trend interpretation | Confirm active definition, source and timeframe | Active status must be confirmed |
| Are items being resolved faster? | Tests closure versus resolution handling | Confirm resolution metric and source | Closure may not equal customer resolution |
| What channels are customers using? | Tests channel interpretation | Confirm channel source and mapping | Channel mix does not prove preference |
| Is repeat contact a failure demand issue? | Tests attribution caution | Treat as investigation signal | Repeat contact does not prove cause |
| Can this output support a decision brief? | Tests decision-support threshold | Require source, metric, caveat, confidence and review | Human review required |

